\begin{frame}[fragile]
\frametitle{One structural break (hidden states Markov model)}
Why did these structural breaks happen?\\~\

Shifts in the relative frequency of the word “peace” might be related to changes in legislation, technological improvements, social development, and historical events:
\begin{enumerate}
\item Change in legislation: at the end of the XVIII century, changes in legislation (the USA and GB) made it easier to publish dissent texts (source: \url{https://www.britannica.com/topic/publishing/Spread-of-education-and-literacy#ref28633)}.

\item Technological improvements: several innovations related to publishing happened at the beginning of the XIX century and made it much cheaper (source: \url{https://www.britannica.com/topic/publishing/Spread-of-education-and-literacy#ref28633}).

\item Social development: increase in population size during the XIX century (2x in GB, 5x in the USA) and higher social status associated with reading (source: \url{https://www.britannica.com/topic/publishing/Spread-of-education-and-literacy#ref28633}).
\setcounter{currentenumi}{\theenumi}
\end{enumerate}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}[fragile]
\frametitle{One structural break (hidden states Markov model)}
\begin{enumerate}
\setcounter{enumi}{\thecurrentenumi}
\item Historical events: several major events in American and British history, associated with peace and war, happened around 1816:
\begin{enumerate}
\item War against Great Britain in 1812 (source: \url{https://history.state.gov/milestones/1801-1829/war-of-1812}), part of the world scenario of the Napoleonic Wars.
\item War and against the Barbary States (pirate states in North Africa) in 1816 (source: \url{https://history.state.gov/milestones/1801-1829/barbary-wars})
\item The Rush-Bagot Pact, 1817 and Convention of 1818, between the USA and Great Britain, about patrolling the border with Canada (source: \url{https://history.state.gov/milestones/1801-1829/rush-bagot}).
\item Acquisition of Florida: Treaty of Adams-Onis (1819) and Transcontinental Treaty (1821), a series of border conflicts between Spain and the USA, fueled by the support of Great Britain to the Spanish colonies (source: \url{https://history.state.gov/milestones/1801-1829/florida}).
\end{enumerate}
\end{enumerate}
\end{frame}

